As a creative designer, I draw a lot of my inspiration from traveling and seeing the world. All the experiences collected and the textures, colors, architecture and cultures that I come across and absorb through my travels play a huge role in how I design and cultivate custom experiences for our couples. Travel and adventures
activates the senses and that magical mix of wonder and feeling is always what I aim for in everything that we design and create. 

I was recently on a cruise to Mexico
with @princesscruises via #discoveryprincess and the vibrancy, passion and colors of Mexico and the sea is currently what's still on my mind. Where do you draw your inspiration from? You can view more of the adventures that we had in Mexico via our reels. #medallionclass #princesspartner #discoveryprincess #princesscruises

Our beautiful couples!  The only way to round up our 2022 season recap is to share the beautiful people that made this year so magical and wonderful.  We wouldn’t be able to do what we do without them.  This year was so special because of the relationship that we had with each one of them.  Each exuded so much joy, love and a beat that was just their own.  I always love watching our couples just “be” in their element on their day - joyously laughing and having that loved up glow of being so happy and in love.  It makes what we do so worth it.  To our couples, thank you for choosing us!  We like to think that we make magic happen for all of you but really, y’all are the magic and we’re just the lucky ones to tell your story 🤍

Thank you for following along our #countdownto2023, it’s been a joy to put together these reels that have meant so much to us and our couples this year.

I’ve never shared much about our own wedding journey, but we were that couple that had three weddings due to the pandemic.  We chose to get married on a whim in our backyard on NYE in 2020 and while we didn’t have to deal with postponement issues, we still had to plan for two additional celebrations in the following years. 

We had a large ceremony and small reception in June 2021 and because things were still opening up during that time, we still had to cap our guest list and couldn’t invite everyone that we wanted.  We then had a third celebration in June 2022 with some friends that we wanted to celebrate with, but specifically made it a friends 20 yr celebration vs wedding because by then,  we’d been married for a while and it  didn’t feel quite right to celebrate as a “wedding” again. 

I loved all three celebrations because they were so different and special in their own ways.  We were able to design each day differently, which is obviously a bonus for me (I love putting together beautiful tables for any and every purpose!) I am so grateful to all our family and friends for celebrating with us in so many different ways as well as for the friendors that were part of each celebration. 

But my favorite will always be our wedding on NYE when it was just the two of us.  Just us, just the way we wanted it to be.  I wouldn’t have done it any other way. #grateful #happyanniversary #nyewedding

One of our favorite things about what we do is the romance of it all.  The romance and chemistry shared between our couples, the romance of the day,l and the beautiful tablescapes and settings that we are able to create.  It all comes down to that one magical moment in time when our couples are in utter bliss with each other amongst their family and friends.  Yeap, that’s what does it for us and keeps us coming back for more✨
